<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="222" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1014,1471]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1194,1219]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">Comments.</emphasis>
The species was originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[833,895,1194,1219]" name="Israel" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">Israel</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kaplan" box="[912,1218,1194,1219]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" refString="Kaplan, M. &amp; Thompson, F. C. (1981) New Syrphidae from Israel (Diptera). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 83, 198 - 212." type="journal article" year="1981">
Kaplan &amp; Thompson 
<number box="[1161,1218,1195,1219]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and first recorded for Europe by 
<bibRefCitation author="Speight" box="[322,494,1230,1255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" refString="Speight, M. C. D. (2013) Species accounts of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 2013. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae. Vol. 72. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin, 216 pp." type="book" year="2013">
Speight (
<number box="[425,486,1231,1255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who cites it from Evros province in North Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1102,1181,1231,1255]" name="Greece" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">Greece</collectingCountry>
(M. De Courcy, pers. comm.). Later, van Steenis &amp; van 
<bibRefCitation author="Steenis" box="[539,702,1266,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" refString="van Steenis J &amp; van Steenis, W. (2014) Two new West-Palaearctic species of Brachyopa, Meigen 1822 (Diptera, Syrphidae) with description and records of additional European species. Norwegian Journal of Entomology, 61, 42 - 52." type="journal article" year="2014">
Steenis (
<number box="[634,693,1267,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
published a record of a taxon related to 
<taxonomicName box="[1160,1373,1266,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculosa">
<emphasis box="[1160,1373,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">B. quadrimaculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Samos Island based on one female. They indicated that this taxon differs morphologically from 
<taxonomicName box="[1262,1386,1302,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernalis">
<emphasis box="[1262,1386,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">B. vernalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
van Steenis &amp; van Steenis and 
<taxonomicName box="[472,690,1338,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculosa">
<emphasis box="[472,690,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">B. quadrimaculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. After studying a 
<typeStatus box="[912,1008,1339,1363]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1055,1272,1338,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculosa">
<emphasis box="[1055,1272,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">B. quadrimaculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(male, 
<collectingCountry box="[1367,1432,1338,1363]" name="Israel" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">Israel</collectingCountry>
, Mongort, 
<date box="[264,426,1374,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" value="1976-03-04">
<number box="[264,278,1375,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" value="4.0">4</number>
March 
<number box="[367,426,1374,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</date>
, leg. A. Friedberg &amp; M. Kaplan, coll. 
<collectingCountry box="[863,923,1375,1399]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">
<collectionCode box="[863,923,1375,1399]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/ze71-842p" name="Tel-Aviv University" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">TAU</collectionCode>
</collectingCountry>
), it can be confirmed that this specimen does not belong to an undescribed species but is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName box="[839,1053,1410,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculosa">
<emphasis box="[839,1053,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="222">B. quadrimaculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The diagnostic characters of this species are presented in the key (see below).
</paragraph>
